<p style=3D"line-height:24px;color:#2A3034;margin:1em 0">The Israeli claim =
to defend the Druze seems to conceal a deeper agenda aimed at redrawing the=
 Syrian map, part of Netanyahu=E2=80=99s vow on Oct. 8, 2023, to transform =
the Middle East. Hours before the more recent Israeli bombing, Druze religi=
ous authorities and military factions rejected secession and affirmed that =
they are an integral part of Syria. They also endorsed the government=E2=80=
=99s activation of the Interior Ministry and judicial police in Sweida prov=
ince, a stronghold of the Druze community, to ensure public security and st=
ability. Sweida=E2=80=99s governor confirmed their appeals for civil peace =
and rejection of violence.</p>
<p style=3D"line-height:24px;color:#2A3034;margin:1em 0"><strong>Seeing Bey=
ond the Druze</strong></p>
<p style=3D"line-height:24px;color:#2A3034;margin:1em 0">Israel seems to be=
 operating under the assumption that dismantling Syria =E2=80=93 which Isra=
el=E2=80=99s finance minister listed as one of the country=E2=80=99s goals =
several days before the belated bombing =E2=80=93 would shield Israel from =
its adversaries, ending the more than century-old conflict with Arabs. Neta=
nyahu also fears that inaction would leave Syria=E2=80=99s fate to be decid=
ed by Turkey, a key ally of the new Syrian regime, but wants to avoid a dir=
ect conflict with Ankara.</p>
